Guys, I have a theory:
The parts that 2-D sings feel like Murdoc is singing to the group or 2-D I'm sorry, also that he feels lonely after being in jail, and now he is trying to reconnect with them or with 2-D.
For example in the part that says, "trying to hold on to you" or "all my ghosts are blue" I think he tells it to 2-d.
Then we see that Fatoumata sings:
"But dear I don't want to die", "I'm going to have my lame"
So it sounds like Murdoc asked 2-d to forgive him but 2-D is so happy now compared to before he doesn't want to.
That´s the theory, thank you for wasting your time reading this.
